<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-755-370  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 755 370.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Industrial Computing  July 1990 p25(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FMS: back in vogue? (flexible manufacturing system)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lawrence, Andrew.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Interest in flexible manufacturing systems (FMSs) is on the rise.andO;A full FMS with several machining centers linked together andunder full computer control and automatic material handling isstill rare, but FMS cells, which are not as complicated, arebecoming more popular.andP;  FMS is on the upswing because thedefinition of FMS has expanded; the technology has improved; usersare less skeptical; and it costs less than it used to.andP;  FMS offershigher throughput and flexibility.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ManufacturingFlexible Manufacturing SystemsTrendsRobots.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>